description:
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to work for a Trust where you can be proud of the contribution you will make to delivering high quality healthcare with a personal touch? Come and join a Trust which recognises the contribution our Health Care Assistants make, and values the work they do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is reflected in our current 5 year strategy vision “to develop a valued and respected workforce who are given the skills to inspire and innovate across professions”.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a flexible, highly motivated individual to join the theatre team at Hexham General Hospital, working with and supporting the Nursing and Medical team. Previous theatre experience is not essential as there is a comprehensive training programme in place, however previous experience in a care environment is preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Criteria (band 2)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication skills both written and verbal&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NVQ II Training Course (or attainment of required competence) within 12 months/NVQ III (or attainment of required competence) in second year to progress to band 3&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work as a team member&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Criteria (band 3)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NVQ Level 3 in Health/Health &amp; Social Care/Direct Care or portfolio of equivalent experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Courses and experience that demonstrate transferable skills i.e. respiratory essentials, basic stoma care, palliative care course for HCAs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous care experience preferably in a healthcare setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;PLEASE NOTE THAT WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE VACANCIES PRIOR TO THE ADVERTISED CLOSING DATE WHEN WE ARE IN RECEIPT OF SUFFICIENT APPLICATIONS&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 9th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameGary RobinsonJob titleTheatre Team ManagerEmail addressgary.robinson@northumbria-healthcare.nhs.ukTelephone number01434 65 5390&lt;/p&gt;
